---
import ServiceLayout from '../../components/ServiceLayout.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Art Therapy"
  description="Sensorimotor art therapy in Pakenham. Creative expression as a pathway to healing, regulation, and growth for children, youth and adults."
  image="/images/services/art-therapy.webp"
>
  <img src="/images/services/art-therapy.webp" alt="Art Therapy at Adventure Therapy Services" class="hero-image" />

  <h2>Creative Expression for Healing and Growth</h2>
  <p>At Adventure Therapy Services, our art therapy sessions use sensorimotor approaches to support regulation, self-expression, and wellbeing. Art provides a powerful, non-verbal way to explore emotions, build confidence, and develop coping strategies.</p>

  <p>Our sessions are facilitated by qualified practitioners who understand how creative activities can support therapeutic goals. Whether painting, drawing, sculpting, or other creative mediums, each session is tailored to the individual's needs and interests.</p>

  <h2>Who Can Benefit?</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Children and young people who find verbal expression challenging</li>
    <li>Individuals experiencing anxiety, stress, or emotional regulation difficulties</li>
    <li>People recovering from trauma or difficult life experiences</li>
    <li>Anyone looking to develop self-awareness and coping strategies through creative means</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What to Expect</h2>
  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">1</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Initial Assessment</h3>
        <p>We begin with an assessment to understand your goals, interests, and therapeutic needs. This helps us tailor the art therapy experience to you.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">2</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Personalised Sessions</h3>
        <p>Each session is designed around your individual goals. We use a range of art materials and techniques to support sensory regulation, emotional expression, and skill development.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">3</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Ongoing Support</h3>
        <p>We work collaboratively with you, your family, and other support networks to ensure the benefits of art therapy carry over into everyday life.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>Please check our <a href="/faqs/">frequently asked questions</a> page for information on our fees & charges and anything you're unsure of.</p>
</ServiceLayout>
